div.p:
This piece in all its Deſigns, aims at what is great and generous, and is founded partly upon Truth; many of the material Circumſtances having been really acted at Genoa but few years ago: It inſiſts chiefly upon two Subjects;

 the effects of an unparallel'd Friendſhip; and the Force, and Reward of Conſtant Love. It appear'd firſt of all in French; and tho now naturaliz'd into our good-natur'd Climat, and become Engliſh, yet it has loſt nothing of its French Vanity, and Preſumption, but daringly hopes to crow'd into your Honour's Cloſet, there

 expecting the happy Time when, Madam, you will be pleas'd to throw away ſome ſpare moments.
